NAME
     lpshut - Stops the LP scheduler

SYNOPSIS
     /usr/lib/lpshut

DESCRIPTION
     lpshut shuts down the printer service. All printers that are
     printing at the time lpshut is invoked will stop printing.
     When lpsched is started again, requests that were printing
     at the time a printer was shut down will be reprinted from
     the beginning.

FILES
     /usr/spool/lp/*

SEE ALSO
     accept(1M), enable(1), lp(1), lpadmin(1M), lpstat(1).
     ``Printer Spooling System" in the TI System V
     Administrator's Guide.


